@startuml Plugin-Minimal-Classes

' ===== Enums =====
enum ExecType { 
 service
 job 
}
enum PlanOpType { 
 Install
 Start
 Reconfigure
 RunJob
 Stop
 Uninstall 
}
enum PluginState {
 starting
 running
 stopped
 error
}

' ===== DTOs / simple types =====
class Json
class RpcMsg
class Endpoint
class DataOpts
class ApplyResult
class ManagerStatus

' ===== CP payload =====
class PluginSpec {
  + plugin_id      : string
  + execType       : ExecType    ' requested mode (service|job)
  + schema_version : string
  + config         : Json        ' plugin-specific JSON (opaque to Agent)
}
note right of PluginSpec
 Single plugin entry from the Control Plane
end note

class PluginSet {
  + version : uint64
  + specs   : vector<PluginSpec>
  + policy  : Json              ' e.g. {"onModuleError":"bypass"}
}
note right of PluginSet
  Atomic desired state from CP. Agent applies only if version increases.
  For MVP, policy can be a simple JSON blob (bypass/drop, uninstall removed, etc.).
end note

' ===== Catalog metadata (static, non-runtime) =====
class PluginDescriptor {
  + id               : string    ' resolved plugin_id (e.g., "acl")
  + version          : string    ' local plugin package version
  + entry            : string    ' path to binary or in-proc symbol
  + schema           : Json      ' optional JSON Schema for config
  + needsDataChannel : bool      ' true if plugin wants a high-rate data path
  ' (OPTIONAL later) + capabilities : uint64  ' bitmask (hot-reload, uses nft/tc, etc.)
}
note right of PluginDescriptor
  Static metadata read from local plugin manifest.
  No runtime fields here. Does not depend on CP payload.
end note

' ===== Runtime handle =====
class PluginHandle {
  + id            : string      ' plugin_id
  + state         : PluginState
  + execType      : ExecType
  + pid           : int
  + configHash    : string      ' stable hash of last applied config
  + session       : IpcSession*
  + dataChannel   : DataChannel*
  + lastHeartbeat : time
  + restartCount  : int
}
note right of PluginHandle
  Runtime record for a running instance, managed by PluginSupervisor.
  Agent/Manager uses this to diff desired vs current and to send commands.
end note

' ===== Core components =====
class PluginRegistry {
  + listInstalled() : vector<PluginDescriptor>
  + resolve(pluginId: string) : optional<PluginDescriptor>
  + validatePackage(pkg) : void                 ' sig/hash check
  + install(pkg) : void                         ' download/unpack/register
  + uninstall(pluginId: string) : void
  --
  - installedPlugins : vector<PluginDescriptor> ' local catalog cache
}
note right of PluginRegistry
  Package/catalog layer only.
  - Knows what plugins are installed and their manifests.
  - Can install/uninstall packages at runtime.
  - Does NOT start processes or hold runtime state.
end note

class PluginSupervisor {
  + start(desc: PluginDescriptor, execType: ExecType) : PluginHandle
  + startOnce(desc: PluginDescriptor, config: Json) : int  ' for job plugins
  + stop(h: PluginHandle, reason: string) : void
  + restart(h: PluginHandle) : void
  + isAlive(h: PluginHandle) : bool
}
note right of PluginSupervisor
  Process lifecycle controller.
  - Spawns service or job processes
  - Wires IpcSession on connect
  - Tracks pid/heartbeats and restarts per policy
end note

abstract class IpcServer {
  + start(endpoint: Endpoint) : void
  + stop() : void
  + sessions() : vector<IpcSession*>
  + onPluginConnected(s: IpcSession) : void
  + onPluginMessage(s: IpcSession, msg: RpcMsg) : void
  ' (OPTIONAL) + onPluginDisconnected(s: IpcSession) : void
}
note right of IpcServer
  Control-channel listener (UDS on POSIX; TCP loopback on Windows for MVP).
  Emits callbacks to PluginManager for handshake and inbound messages.
end note

class IpcSession {
  + peerId : string
  + send(msg: RpcMsg) : void
  + close() : void
}
note right of IpcSession
  One full-duplex control stream per plugin instance (JSON-RPC framed).
end note

class DataChannel {
  + open(opts: DataOpts) : void
  + close() : void
}
note right of DataChannel
  Optional high-rate channel, only opened if plugin declares it needs one.
  Keep control (JSON-RPC) and data channels separate.
end note

class PluginManager {
  + init(endpoint: Endpoint) : void
  + applyPluginSet(set: PluginSet) : ApplyResult
  + getStatus() : ManagerStatus
  --
  - computeConfigHash(cfg: Json) : string
  - diff(desired: vector<PluginSpec>) : Plan
  - execute(plan: Plan) : ApplyResult
  - configure(handle: PluginHandle, cfg: Json) : void
}
note right of PluginManager
  Orchestrator (brains).
  - Receives PluginSet from CP
  - Ensures packages exist (via Registry)
  - Builds an ordered Plan (Install/Start/Reconfigure/RunJob/Stop/Uninstall)
  - Executes Plan (uses Supervisor + IpcServer)
  - Sends 'configure' over control channel; opens DataChannel if needed
end note

' ===== Relations =====
PluginManager --> PluginRegistry
PluginManager --> PluginSupervisor
PluginManager --> IpcServer
PluginSupervisor --> PluginHandle
PluginHandle --> IpcSession
PluginHandle --> DataChannel

@enduml
